        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "content": "CHAPTER ONE",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "600",
                  "id": "tm8xX",
                  "letterSpacing": 3,
                  "name": "chapterLabel",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "content": "The Last Frontier",
                  "fill": "#1E293B",
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 36,
                  "fontWeight": "500",
                  "id": "CBjlV",
                  "name": "chapterTitle",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "fill": "#3B82F6",
                  "height": 2,
                  "id": "Bz86q",
                  "name": "divider",
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "width": 60
                },
                {
                  "content": "The observation deck of Station Aria offered a view that never grew old. Marcus Cole stood at the reinforced viewport, hands clasped behind his back, watching the slow rotation of Kepler-9 below. The planet's surface — a patchwork of ochre deserts and deep violet seas — caught the light of its twin suns in ways that still surprised him after three years.",
                  "fill": "#334155",
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "id": "ffcaK",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "name": "para1",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "type": "text",
                  "width": "fill_container"
                },
                {
                  "content": "\"Commander.\" Elena's voice came from behind him, quiet but urgent. He didn't need to turn around to know she was holding a datapad with results she didn't want to say aloud. The tension in that single word told him everything.",
                  "fill": "#334155",
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "id": "TFoJN",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "name": "para2",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "type": "text",
                  "width": "fill_container"
                },
                {
                  "content": "\"Show me,\" he said, still facing the viewport. The reflection in the glass was enough — he could see her expression, the way her jaw tightened as she extended the tablet. Numbers he'd been dreading. Numbers that changed everything.",
                  "fill": "#334155",
                  "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "id": "wY4wH",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "name": "para3",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "type": "text",
                  "width": "fill_container"
                }
              ],
              "effect": {
                "blur": 20,
                "color": "#00000020",
                "offset": {
                  "x": 0,
                  "y": 2
                },
                "shadowType": "outer",
                "type": "shadow"
              },
              "fill": "#FFFDF9",
              "gap": 24,
              "height": "fill_container",
